library(terra)
library(gdalUtilities)
library(tidyverse)
library(ggcorrplot)
library(ggfortify)


We obtained surface reflectance data from Sentinel-2, with native spatial resolutions of 10–20 m. Low-quality pixels (e.g., clouds, shadows) were removed using the quality assurance bands. Annual mean composites for 2024 were created for the 10 optical bands (Blue, Green, Red, NIR, four Red Edge bands, and two SWIR bands), which were subsequently resampled to 100 m.
We further computed the 2024 Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) from the same Sentinel-2 source. After masking low-quality pixels, NDVI was calculated for each image, aggregated to an annual mean, and resampled to 100 m.


